latestIgtvVideos.title: Mango Mousse 😋
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
First of all sorry for keeping you all waiting this long 🙈
cheese cake one of my fav desserts Which I use to make on eid 
But guess what happened , I forgot to add cheese (I was more into shooting)🙈🙈
So here are the measurements : 
1. Digestive Buscuit / marrie gold - I've used Lulu's Digestive Biscuit 1 pack.
2. Butter 50 gram 
3. 4 mangoes (3 for mango puree , 1 for topping) 
4. Whipping cream - (250ml) 
5. Condensed Milk - half tin 
6. Nestle's tin cream (unflavoured ) -2 tin 320grams 
7. Gelatin - 20 grams in total -Second layer 10-12 grams , third layer 3-4 grams and Topping 4- 5 grams . As I mentioned in the video, I didn't want it to be more hard so you can increase/adjust it to 30 grams.Or you Can Add China Grass instead of Gelatin
8. Vanilla Extract - 1 teaspoon
•———•———•———•———•———•———•
Please note that : I've Reduced the amount of sweet in my recipe because I don't want to go high on sugar😅
So you can adjust the amount of sugar or condensed milk upto you😊🤗

latestIgtvVideos.title: Simple Biscuit Pudding with 5 ingredients
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Craving For tea time's mahalabia ? 
I am a big time fan of tea time's Mahalabia and I thought of trying with my own Recipe and Alhamdulillah It's almost the same Taste of
Mahalabia 😍😋 All you Want is :
For The pudding Base (cream) :
1.Whipped Cream - 1 cup (250ml)
2. @nestledessertsarabia 's Unflavoured tin cream Original - 2 no's (each tin 160g ) total Of 320g of cream 
Any unflavoured cream of Your Choice would Go 
I usually Use Puck , Nestle and Rainbow
3. @rainbowmilk sweetened Condensed milk - Half tin (approx 200g)
4. 1 teaspoon of Vanilla extract 
To dip the biscuit : 
1. One bowl of Warm water with 2 pinch of salt and 1-2 Tablespoon of milk (milk is optional ) 
Biscuit :
3 packets of @britanniaarabia 50-50 biscuit 
You can choose 
Any biscuit with a bit of salty taste .
